===Etymology===
{{liushu|p}} – hand and fingers. The top stroke is the bent over middle finger, while the horizontal strokes are each two fingers. Compare [[爪]], [[寸]], [[九]].

Note that unlike the other hand/claw characters, 手 has consistently had five fingers: a mammalian/human hand, as opposed to the three digits often found in the others.

Compare also {{term|止||foot|sc=Hani}}, derived from a footprint, originally composed of 3 toes and a sole.

